“Malachite, you’re being unreasonable—“
“*Unreasonable!?*” Malachite shouts, slamming his fist on the table angrily, interrupting Shale. He extends his other hand outwards behind him. “Morise is *in there!* If we do this now, *they don’t stand a chance!* WHY ARE NONE OF YOU LISTENING TO ME!?—“
“Because what you’re suggesting we do is *insane.* Going there right now is a damn death wish. We’re all tired, and with Illuvies and Castus still fighting...”
Shale looks down, biting her lip for a moment before wrapping an arm around her self, and looking away as she thinks about the possibilities. “It’s too much. We need rest. We’re all tired, and we just need a break. Anything right now... a lot of us could get seriously injured, maybe even ki—“
Malachite snarls, and he interrupts Shale in his impatience. “WHO *CARES*!?”

Malachite’s glasses fall off of his head, hitting the ground and cracking against it. His face is tilted to the side, eyes widened in surprise as he brings a hand up, carefully touching the now dark pink mark on his face.
Shale growls at him, hand still out and lingering after the slap. “If Polaris were here, he’d do the same damn thing.”
With that, she walks away, leaving alone Malachite to think about it.

Venor snorts and twirls in the air, coming to a stop with a kick that sends her opponent flying. “See? I’m elegant.” She slams her elbow into her next attacker’s face, followed by a punch to the gut courtesy of Careless Whisper. “Of course you are.” Lamia sighs, dealing with his opponents. “That was sarcastic.” Venor rolls all of her eyes, opening her shoulder ones for effect, then immediately closes them as she rams someone with her right shoulder. “I don’t like it when people are sarcastic to me.” She twists round and drives her knee into the poor guy’s gut. 

“Isn’t that slightly hypocritical, though?” Lamia points out, and someone grabs Venor around the shoulders. She uses the wall as leverage, running up it. Well, running up the guy who she was fighting against it anyway. “I’m like that. And I could hypnotize you to think otherwise. But I-” She steps on his face and knocks his head back against the wall, simultaneously ripping herself out of the woman’s grip and flipping behind her.

“I don’t. It’s proof of my niceness.” Someone punches her gut and she turns around, furiously jabbing a strike into their throat, following it up by sweeping their legs out from under them and stomping repeatedly on their face. “How dare you! How dare you hit me, you stupid fucker!” She yells at them, and Lamia folds his arms, amused. “Very nice.” Venor sends a final kick into the person’s side, and turns to him. “Shut up.” 

Lamia has dealt with the woman for her. That was nice of him. “What do you want?” Venor asks suspiciously. “What do you mean?” Lamia’s acting innocent. “You negated the other threat for me. You usually stand back and watch me struggle.” Venor points out. “What do you want?” 

Lamia chuckles and decides against patting her head patronisingly. A sure sign of friendship. “You could buy me lunch.” He suggests, and Venor scowls. “Fine. Only because I owe you one, though.”

She spends a few minutes talking about the best ways to prank people, and Spira nods, grinning at one. “I’ll try that next.” Shale nods back. “Good choice. Minimal damage, maximum chaos. Employ the twins.” She laughs, and then Spira goes pale. 
“Hi… Mom.” 

Shale turns around and sees Cerise standing in the doorway, hands on her hips. “Oh… Shit. How much did you hear, babe?” Shale sweats nervously. The look on Cerise’s face is enough. “Scatter!” Shale yells, and throws a book at her wife while her son climbs through the window. Shale isn’t far behind.

Morise placed an unconscious Superbia in the arms of their attendant and he scurried off as they marched forward, hair floating out behind them as they marched down the hallway, in their tall, dark form. Their footsteps made no sound in the air as they opened the door, standing in the darkened room before the Eternal Council. Their dark form blended in perfectly, only their mismatched eyes glowing in the darkness. 

***Have you figured out who you are, Moria?***
The Plasma of Time’s voice grated around in their head. Morise refused to close one eye, as they normally did. It showed weakness.

**Your form?**
__*Yourself?*__ 

The Plasmas of Matter and Physics added, and Morise blinked to themself in the darkness. *No longer Moria, Eternals.* 
There was a pause.

***Then?***

Morise allowed their eyes to glow brighter. 
*My name is Morise. Gender is no longer an issue to me, nor is age. My form is meaningless. I have not settled on one, but I do not need a form to be heard throughout the reaches of space and time. I may not have defeated the Outposts, but that’s because I am above them. They do not need rulers; it is not the Plasma’s duty to rule. It is our duty to observe and keep reality in balance.* 

Another pause.
*__You have passed.__*
**Welcome to the Council...**
***Morise.*** 

And in the darkness, Morise grinned.

Ombrage was walking in the empty halls of the sleeping areas, stopping by Polaris' room for a bit. He was gone, she knew it, but she wished she could've seen him before he went away.
As she was getting lost in her thoughts, a hand grabbed her shoulder, and a way to familiar voice whispered in her hear "Well, well, well, it has been a while my dear Ombrage" Superbia was grinning as Ombrage turned around to face her, 'no no PLEASE NO' she thought, she was alone with her, and paralysed by fear. 
"Now that your little knights in shinning armor are gone, I can finally have some fun ! ~" Superbia'm cackled as her stand launched on Ombrage, and in a blink, she was trapped in the Mist.
Once her eyes were opened, she looked around her, she was... In the forest ? "that's... Strange..." She muttered, where was the empty White void she has gotten so used to ? Why was she in the forest ? Has she dreamt everything to this point ? Despite her location being a place of peace, she couldn't help but feel on edge.
She started to carefully walk through the forest, and soon started to notice.. Something. The more she was looking around, the more thorns she could see, everywhere. Thorns on the trees, running through the grounds, and soon enough, giant walls of vines with thorns, getting closer and closer to her. Ombrage was starting to feel the panic getting to her, her heart was beating faster and faster, her only thought was to run, run as far from these as she could, and ran she did. She ran where there was no thorns in sight, ending up at a small clearing, she could here caughing nearby.

"S-shade-" a familiar voice whispered through the forest, Ombrage ran up to the voice, "Barselius ! Are you alright ? What are you doing here ?" She was relieved to see a familiar face around, she grabbed the plasma's arm.
"I'm. I'm fine shade, don't worry-" he caughed again, blood dripping from his mouth "You aren't ! I-I'll take you to the hospital-"
"doubt it'll be possible" The plasma respond, pointing at his feet. A vines with thorns was slowly wraping around his leg, thorns sinking in his skin and a pool of blood was forming on the ground. Ombrage panicked, she wasn't letting him fall into the thorns' trap, so she desperatly attempt to cut it with her daggers, but every cut only made the thorns go faster and faster. She was lost in helping her friend, she barely noticed the ones making their way on her leg until she felt a piercing pain in her ankle "No no no no please no ! Get away get away-" She fell back and started sobbing as she attempt to cut it off, her heart beating fast and loud, she looked at the thorned walls getting closer to her, and she wrap herself into a ball and cried, cried like it was the end for her.
A sinister laughed echoed through the forest, as the Mist disapeared in the blink of an eye, and Ombrage was back to the sleeping areas. Superbia grabbed Ombrage's face with one hand, forcing her to look at her in the eyes "My oh my, this was fun ! ~" She licked a tear off Ombrage's cheek, smiling "Your tears are as delicious as ever"
Superbia  finally let go off her, and walked away, leaving Ombrage alone again. She slowly and weakly got up, feeling disgusted, ashamed and humiliated. She walked to her room, locked the door and crashed on her bed, wraping herself in the covers, trying to fall asleep and hoping to not wake up again.

The tall mun kneeled in front of the statue of the one who once was her dearest friend. She gently put down her guitar, the one who played so many tunes for so long... It still had his words on it. Her expression was, blank, and while her eyes were red from crying, it was clear they were as dry as the desert now.
After a while of pure silent, where only the forest would speak, she got up, and finally spoke, her voice was dry and full of guilt and anger
"I know that death is unkind, unfair and unpredictible, but you never deserved it. This why I will make sure they all stare at the Reaper right in the eyes"
And with that, she left, a heart full of new determination to avenge the one she had considered a father in those hard times.

A young girl lost in her dreams, always having her head in the clouds, daydreaming by Day and occasionally lucid dreaming at night.
Her dreams are always crazy and strange, but with a sort of peotic feel to them.
When she's lucid dreaming, she never directly impact her dreams, and simply enjoy exploring and being free. Although, occasionally, she does mess with the reality of her dreams slightly. Her dreams are often empty of People, devoided of humans. All there is are vague humanoid shapes, with little to no consciousness.
One Day, Margaux notice a human shaped unlike any other, their mouvements are clear, and their face detailed, almost like they were someone dreaming too.
However, it seemed Margaux couldn't talk to the figure, as if she didn't exist to their eyes. Even stranger, she could not make this figure bend to her will. 
Howerver, she managed to observe the figure, and upon a closer look, it seem like the figure was a woman around Margaux's age.
Convinced to find out what is happening, Margaux goes on a Journey to find out the woman's indentity, while exploring more in depth the strange world of dreams
